{"name":"Backstab","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A <em>backstab</em> attempt with a class 1 or 2 melee weapon. The target must be unaware of attack, which may be the result of <em>hiding</em> or <em>moving silently</em>. Also, the target must have vital organs (e.g., <strong>skeleton</strong>, <strong>zombie</strong> exempt) and a discernible &ldquo;back&rdquo; (e.g., <strong>green slime</strong>, <strong>purple worm</strong> exempt). If the requirements are met, the following benefits result:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The attack roll is made at +4 &ldquo;to hit.&rdquo;</li>\n<li>Additional weapon damage dice are rolled according to the purloiner&rsquo;s level of experience:\n<ul>\n<li>1st to 4th levels = &times;2</li>\n<li>5th to 8th levels = &times;3</li>\n<li>9th to 12th levels = &times;4</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Other damage modififiers (strength, sorcery, etc.) are added afterwards (e.g., a 5th-level purloiner with 13 strength and a <strong>+1 short sword</strong> rolls 3d6+2).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579316564,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"06Z9qmGKbj3zFkIz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">.</span></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 105\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579316564,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"1xlf0BJp0NBFvEvH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Turn Undead","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 109\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 109\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 3rd level, exert control over the undead, causing them to flee and/or cower. At 3rd level the purloiner has 1st-level turning abil- ity (TA 1); at 4th level, TA 2; and so on. Evil purloiners can opt instead to compel the submission and service of these foul creatures. In either case, t<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">he purloiner must do the following:</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>Stand before the undead (within 30 feet)</li>\n<li>Speak boldly a commandment whilst displaying a holy symbol</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The referee must cross-reference the purloiner&rsquo;s <em>turning ability</em> (TA) with the <em>Undead Type</em> to determine the purloiner&rsquo;s chance of success. The referee may ask the player to roll a d12 to determine the outcome, or the result may be fixed. The results are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">d12 score equal to/less than the number indicated: <strong>T (turned)</strong></span></li>\n<li>d12 score greater than the number indicated: <strong>NT (not turned)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Undead Turning Definitions:</strong><br>The following definitions apply to Table 13:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><strong>NT (not turned):</strong> the undead are beyond the purloiner&rsquo;s power to affect.</span></li>\n<li><strong>T (turned):</strong> 2d6 undead are compelled to cower/flee for 1 turn unless attacked.</li>\n<li><strong>D (destroyed):</strong> 2d6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n<li><strong>UD (ultimate destruction):</strong> 1d6+6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>N.B.: Purloiners of above-average charisma (15+) are more commanding; hence, their chance-in-twelve of success is improved by one (+1); e.g., a 4-in-12 chance becomes 5-in-12 (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>charisma</em>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Frequency of Undead Turning:</strong> This ability can be used a number of times per day equal to the character&rsquo;s TA; however, the purloiner can make but one attempt per encounter unless a second wave of undead arrive.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 13: Turn Undead</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p. 33]</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>How to Turn Multiple Undead Types:</strong> If multiple kinds of undead are met in a single encounter, only one d12 roll is required. The same result is applied to each <em>Undead Type</em>. Those of the lowest <em>Undead Type</em> are affected first, unless the sorcerer specifically targets a single creature, in which case only that creature potentially is affected (e.g., if a <strong>vampire</strong> stands at the fore of a pack of <strong>zombies</strong>, the cleric might step forth, holy symbol raised, and speak a commandment of abolishment, pointing a holy symbol directly at the <strong>vampire</strong>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Evil Command of Undead:</strong> A purloiner of Evil alignment may opt to exercise control over the undead on a successful <em>turn undead</em> check. Such undead remain under the sorcerer&rsquo;s sway unless <em>turned</em> or <em>commanded</em> by another sorcerer of equal or greater turning ability. Up to 2 HD of undead per TA level can be controlled. If a Neutral purloiner attempts to <em>command undead</em>, then he or she will have turned to a darker path, submitting to Evil and no longer of Neutral alignment; consequences may ensue.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner 3+","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"9rKcPUie7EkgUHNz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Discern Noise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To hearken at a door and detect the faintest of noises on the other side, perceive the distant footfalls of a wandering monster, or distinguish a single voice in a crowd. Six rounds (one minute) of concentrated listening are required.</p>\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rdWUP52trHy6v2d4"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253207156,"modifiedTime":1681579316564,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"AtxvF98j3MGlflCk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Open Locks","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To pick locks or disable latching mechanisms both magical and mundane. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required. Picking or dismantling a lock may be attempted but once; if the attempt fails, the purloiner cannot try again until he has gained a level of experience. Most locks require 1d4 minutes to pick; complex locks might necessitate 3d6 minutes.</p>\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.U32lI37JFJAFhB7v"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253307994,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"DOd4SDDeuquAZUVr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Magic Item Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 108\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Can utilize magic items normally restricted to clerics.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"EVPz2fWH1Rn6GZHX","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Decipher Script","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To translate texts otherwise not understood. Maps can be interpreted, instructions decoded, and so forth. Ancient or alien languages, however, may remain unintelligible, lacking any basis for comparison.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 101\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ty9A9s3vbBBtVdke"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253152433,"modifiedTime":1681579316564,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"EWU4sA73puR7OTXp","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Hide","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To vanish into shadows, camouflage oneself, or flatten one&rsquo;s body to a seemingly impossible degree&mdash;all whilst remaining still as a statue. Only the slightest movement is permissible (e.g., unsheathing a blade, opening a pouch). Hiding is impossible in direct sunlight, or if the purloiner is observed.</p>\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XlGOODo5lRFAjzfD"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253228973,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"G2oLjz6pjN5IiJ5N","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Detect Secret Doors","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 96\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Find a secret door on a base 3-in-6 chance.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579316564,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"IbeGVJHE2OOd9xmA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Thieves' Cant","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The secret language of thieves, a strange pidgin in which some words may be unintelligible to an ignorant listener, whereas others might be common yet of alternative meaning. This covert tongue is used in conjunction with specific body language, hand gestures, and facial expressions. Two major dialects of Thieves&rsquo; Cant are used in Hyperborea: one by city thieves, the other by pirates; commonalities exist betwixt the two.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"NKckGjRxl8Y2Xpwt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Manipulate Traps","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To find, remove, and reset traps both magical and mundane. Separate checks must be made to accomplish each facet of this skill: <em>find</em>, <em>remove</em>, <em>reset</em>. Failure by more than two, or if a natural <em>12</em> is rolled, may cause the trap to detonate on the purloiner. Also, a new trap may be built if the mechanism is simple and the parts available; anything more complex requires the assistance of an engineer. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required when practicing this ability.</p>\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E7f8uy6uqSVICdkP"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253249264,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"QvOAKjwJah5OzqPN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Agile","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+1 AC bonus when unarmoured and unencumbered (small shield allowed).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579316564,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"S75uuFmQtaUDGiAR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke scrolls with spells from the <strong>Cleric Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong>), unless the scroll was created by a thaumaturgical sorcerer (one who casts magician or magician subclass spells).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"aYSmeQPQhTIlcbk2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 32\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 108\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials vary: Some purloiners engrave thin tablets of stone, whereas others use vellum or parchment, a fine quill, and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia. This involved process requires one week per spell level and must be completed on consecrated ground, such as a shrine, fane, or temple.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5svHxLHi8sIn35Uj"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"f1G7An78r6xK3COk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Move Silently","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move with preternatural quiet, even across squeaky floorboards, dry leaves, loose debris, and the like. This skill is executed at half the purloiner&rsquo;s normal movement rate.</p>\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ZjXb3ZhjVCXjN4wl"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253287286,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"fyVivHfpeehj6b8g","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 108\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Purloiners memorize and cast cleric spells, but they do not maintain spell books; rather, they might bear the scriptures of their faiths in prayer books, on sacred <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">scrolls, or on graven tablets. The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 62</strong>, though purloiners of high wisdom gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>wisdom</em>). For example, a 4th-level purloiner with 13 wisdom can cast two level 1 spells and one level 2 spell per day.</span></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 108\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Purloiners begin with knowledge of two level 1 spells, sacred mysteries revealed through initiation into a sect or cult devoted to an otherworldly power, deific being, or ethos. These spells are drawn from the <strong>Cleric Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong>). Purloiners develop two new spells at each level gain. Typically, they are acquired via spiritual revelation, otherworldly favour, or the piecing together of abstract theologies. Such spells are learnt automatically, with no need of qualification rolls, but they must be of castable levels (see <strong>Table 62</strong>).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial no. of spells known: &times;2</li>\n<li>No. of spells gained per level: &times;2</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"lU3wWol43MUtF6Kc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
