{"name":"Pick Pockets","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To filch items from a pocket, pouch, backpack, or garment using nimble fingers and possibly distraction. Failure by a margin of 3 or greater indicates the attempt has been observed (though not necessarily by the victim). If the roll is successful, the referee must determine what has been procured. If a purloiner attempts to pick the pocket of a higher-level thief, legerdemainist, or purloiner, a penalty equal to the difference in levels must be applied to the check. This skill also covers the gamut of sleight-of-hand trickery a thief might employ to deceive onlookers.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Purloiners practice a full range of thievish skills. These abilities improve as the purloiner advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"purloiner","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rdyChXQXhaUyVVrI"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253332581,"modifiedTime":1681579316565,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"z5cVdBkMptf5gZpj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
